
[1]virulent

   VIR'ULENT, a. [L. virulentus, from virus, poison, that is, strength,
   from the same root as vir, vireo. See Venom.]

   1. Extremely active in doing injury; very poisonous or venomous. No
   poison is more virulent than that of some species of serpents.

   2. Very bitter in enmity; malignant; as a virulent invective.
